Parents of children with disabilities in the Eastern Cape have highlighted access to education as one of the biggest challenges they face. As a result, some resort to home schooling their children.Yesterday roads and public works MEC Thandiswa Marawu commemorated Disability Rights Awareness Month by handing out wheelchairs and crutches to 49 people with disabilities in Barkly East.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions